data.name: AbsFoldChange
data.value: Absolute value of the fold change

data.name: AbsLog2FoldChange
data.value: Absolute value of the log base 2 of the fold change

data.name: Abundance
data.value: The value for this replicate which was used to calculate the fold change. The number depends on the normalization method, and whether the fold change is being calculated at the protein or peptide level.

data.name: Accuracy
data.value: Ratio of Calculated Concentration to the specified Analyte Concentration

data.name: AcquiredTime
data.value: Last time and date at which the mass spectrometer began acquiring this replicate data. Or #N/A if the file was imported with a version older than 1.1.

data.name: AdjustedPValue
data.value: P-value adjusted for the multiple comparisons within this group comparison across the multiple peptides or proteins. The adjustment is done using the Benjamini-Hochberg procedure.

data.name: AllInfoMessage
data.value: Detailed description of the change

data.name: AnalyteConcentration
data.value: Known quantity of analyte that was spiked into the external or quality control standard.

data.name: Analyzer
data.value: The type of analyzer that was used to collect the spectrum. If more than one analyzer was used, the names of the analyzers will be separated by slashes.

data.name: Area
data.value: Area under the curve (AUC), minus background, for the transition peak.

data.name: AreaNormalized
data.value: The Area normalized to the sum of the Area values for all transitions in the document.

data.name: AreaRatio
data.value: The ratio of the Area of this transition to its corresponding transition in the first internal standard label type, before version 0.7 this was always light/heavy, and appeared on the heavy transitions.

data.name: AttributeAreaProportion
data.value: The ratio of the normalized area to the sum of the normalized areas of all of the other peptides or molecules in the document that have the same Attribute Area Proportion.

data.name: AttributeGroupId
data.value: Affects the grouping of peptides or molecules in the calculation of Attribute Area Proportion.

data.name: AuditLogDetailRowId
data.value: Id of the detailed message

data.name: AuditLogRow
data.value: Row of audit log information

data.name: AuditLogRowId
data.value: Id of the entry

data.name: AutoSelectMolecules
data.value: If true, then Skyline will automatically add or remove molecules from the Molecule List based on the current settings.

data.name: AutoSelectPeptides
data.value: If true, then Skyline will automatically add or remove peptides based on the Peptide Settings Filter.

data.name: AutoSelectPrecursors
data.value: If true, then Skyline will automatically add or remove precursors based on the Transition Settings Filter, spectral library, etc.

data.name: AutoSelectTransitions
data.value: If true, then Skyline will automatically add or remove transitions from the precursor depending on the Transition Settings Filter, spectral library, etc.

data.name: AverageMassErrorPPM
data.value: Average Mass Error PPM

data.name: AverageMasses
data.value: The modified sequence which specifies modifications with their average masses, e.g. "C[+57.05162]".

data.name: AverageMeasuredRetentionTime
data.value: The average peptide retention time over all replicates

data.name: Background
data.value: The area of the rectangle formed by the integration boundaries, and the baseline and a line perpendicular to minimum intersection intensity between the integration boundaries and the chromatogram for the transition peak.

data.name: BatchFiguresOfMerit
data.value: Figures of merit calculated using the subset of external standard replicates that have the same Batch Name as this replicate.

data.name: BatchLimitOfDetection
data.value: Lower limit of detection calculated using the subset of external standard replicates that have the same Batch Name as this replicate.

data.name: BatchLimitOfQuantification
data.value: Lower limit of quantification calculated using the subset of external standard replicates that have the same Batch Name as this replicate.

data.name: BatchName
data.value: Name of the batch that this replicate belongs to. The calibration curve for a particular replicate will be calculated using the subset of external standards with the same batch name.

data.name: BatchTargetQualitativeIonRatio
data.value: Target Qualitative Ion Ratio calculated using the subset of external standard replicates that have the same Batch Name as this replicate.

data.name: BeginPos
data.value: The zero-based position of the first (N-terminal) amino acid of the peptide within its containing protein sequence, or #N/A if no protein sequence is available.

data.name: BestReplicate
data.value: True if this replicate has the highest overall peptide peak score.

data.name: BestRetentionTime
data.value: The RetentionTime value of the transition with the highest maximum intensity for the precursor.

data.name: CalculatedConcentration
data.value: The concentration of the analyte calculated using either: 1. The calibration curve (if the Peptide Settings > Quantification has a Regression Fit specified) 2. The ratio to internal standard (or surrogate) and multiplying by the Internal Standard Concentration

data.name: CalculatedConcentrationMessage
data.value: Warning if missing data impacts comparisons of the "Calculated Concentration" between replicates

data.name: CalculatedConcentrationRaw
data.value: Calculated concentration value available even when missing data impacts comparisons between replicates

data.name: CalculatedConcentrationStrict
data.value: Calculated concentration value unavailable when missing data impacts comparisons between replicates

data.name: CalibrationCurve
data.value: Calibration Curve that was calculated using Replicates whose Sample Type was "Standard" and that had an "Analyte Concentration" specified.

data.name: CandidatePeakGroup
data.value: A set of peaks with the same start and end time from the transition chromatograms of a set of precursors belonging to the same peptide or molecule.

data.name: CAS
data.value: Standardized molecular identifier

data.name: Chosen
data.value: True if the peak boundaries of the candidate peak are the same as the integration boundaries that are used for all of the transitions in the peak group.

data.name: Chromatogram
data.value: Chromatogram for the transition and replicate.

data.name: ChromatogramEndTime
data.value: Last retention time in the chromatogram

data.name: ChromatogramExtractionWidth
data.value: Full width of the channel over which the spectrum intensities were summed

data.name: ChromatogramIonMobility
data.value: Center of the ion mobility window that was used to filter spectra during chromatogram extraction

data.name: ChromatogramIonMobilityExtractionWidth
data.value: Full width of the ion mobility window that was used to filter spectra during chromatogram extraction

data.name: ChromatogramIonMobilityUnits
data.value: Units of the chromatogram ion mobility and chromatogram ion mobility extraction width

data.name: ChromatogramPrecursorMz
data.value: Precursor m/z of the chromatogram

data.name: ChromatogramProductMz
data.value: Product m/z of the chromatogram

data.name: ChromatogramSource
data.value: Type of scans from which the chromatogram was extracted: one of "fragment", "sim", "ms1", or "unknown"
data.comment: Keep the english form of "fragment", "sim", "ms1", or "unknown" because that is what users see in the Document Grid. However, maybe put the localized translation in parentheses: "fragment" (translation of fragment), "sim" (translation of selected ion monitoring), etc.

data.name: ChromatogramStartTime
data.value: First retention time in the chromatogram

data.name: CleavageAa
data.value: Specific amino acid residue in the peptide after (C-terminal of) which the peptide was cleaved upon fragmentation. (e.g. P, M, S, T, etc.)

data.name: Coeluting
data.value: True if this transition's peak has similar apex and extents as the other transitions within the peak group.

data.name: CollisionalCrossSection
data.value: A measure of ion mobility, in square angstroms, which is typically converted to appropriate units (eg drift time, inverseK0) and used in extracting chromatograms from ion mobility mass spectra.

data.name: CollisionCrossSection
data.value: The collision cross section of the precursor

data.name: CollisionEnergy
data.value: Collision Energy for the precursor ion according to instrument/vendor specific default collision energy equation within Skyline

data.name: CompensationVoltage
data.value: The voltage that was applied when the FAIMS spectrum was collected

data.name: ConcentrationMultiplier
data.value: Value to multiply the replicate's "analyte concentration" by in order to get the specific concentration of the specific peptide or molecule.

data.name: ConfidenceLevel
data.value: Confidence level which was used to determine the confidence interval around the fold change.

data.name: CountTruncated
data.value: The number of transitions for a precursor that integrate a peak with a boundary at either end of the acquisition time range, where intensity at the end is greater than 1% of the entire peak height higher than the other extent.

data.name: Cv
data.value: Cv

data.name: CvArea
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the transition Area values.

data.name: CvAreaNormalized
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the transition AreaNormalized values.

data.name: CvAreaRatio
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the transition AreaRatio values.

data.name: CvBestRetentionTime
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the precursor BestRetentionTime values.

data.name: CvFwhm
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the transition Fwhm (peak width) values

data.name: CvMaxFwhm
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the precursor MaxFwhm (peak width) values.

data.name: CvMaxHeight
data.value: Cv Max Height

data.name: CvRetentionTime
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the transition RetentionTime values.

data.name: CvTotalArea
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the precursor TotalArea values

data.name: CvTotalAreaNormalized
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the precursor TotalAreaNormalized values.

data.name: CvTotalAreaRatio
data.value: Coefficient of variation (CV) of the precursor TotalAreaRatio values

data.name: CycleTimeAcrossPeak
data.value: Cycle time (in seconds) across the integrated peak.

data.name: DeclusteringPotential
data.value: Declustering Potential for the precursor ion according to instrument/vendor specific default declustering potential equation within Skyline

data.name: DecoyMzShift
data.value: Shift in m/z applied to the precursor to create the decoy m/z

data.name: DegreesOfFreedom
data.value: Number of degrees of freedom which was used to calculate the confidence interval of the T-test.

data.name: DetailReason
data.value: Detailed reason the user gave for making the change

data.name: Details
data.value: List of detailed change messages and reasons

data.name: DetectionQValue
data.value: A false discovery rate (FDR) score assigned to each chosen target peak after applying a mProphet model.

data.name: DetectionZScore
data.value: A normalized mProphet score assigned to each chosen peak (target and decoy) after applying a mProphet model, expressed as the number of standard deviations (SD) from the mean decoy score.

data.name: DriftTimeFragment
data.value: Ion mobility drift time (in milliseconds) for fragment ions, which typically move faster due to more energetic collisions. (For backward compatibility only: IonMobilityFragment and IonMobilityUnits are the preferred terms.)

data.name: DriftTimeMS1
data.value: Ion mobility drift time (in milliseconds) for precursor ions, which typically move slightly slower than fragment ions as they are less energetic. (For backward compatibility only: IonMobilityMS1 and IonMobilityUnits are the preferred terms.)

data.name: DriftTimeWindow
data.value: Ion mobility drift time window (in milliseconds) used in chromatogram extraction. (For backward compatibility only: IonMobilityWindow and IonMobilityUnits are the preferred terms.)

data.name: EndPos
data.value: The zero-based position of the last (C-terminal) amino acid of the peptide within its containing protein sequence, or #N/A if no protein sequence is available

data.name: EndTime
data.value: Retention time at the ending integration boundary for the transition peak.

data.name: ErrorMessage
data.value: Text of the error message, if any, which occurred while trying to calculate this value.

data.name: EstimatedValue
data.value: Slope of the linear regression.

data.name: ExcludeFromCalibration
data.value: Whether the results in the replicate should be excluded from the peptide's calibration curve calculation.

data.name: ExplicitAnalyteConcentration
data.value: The concentration of this particular molecule or peptide in this particular replicate. If the Explicit Analyte Concentration is not specified then the concentration of the analyte is assumed to be the Analyte Concentration from the Replicate times the Concentration Multiplier of the Peptide or Molecule.

data.name: ExplicitCollisionalCrossSection
data.value: The exact desired collisional cross section (in square angstroms) to be converted to ion mobility and used in extracting chromatograms from ion mobility mass spectra, overriding all model values.

data.name: ExplicitCollisionEnergy
data.value: The exact desired collision energy to be used in SRM methods or transitions lists for a target, overriding all model or optimization library or per-precursor explicit values.

data.name: ExplicitCompensationVoltage
data.value: The exact desired compensation voltage (ion mobility filter) to be used in SRM methods or transitions lists for a target, overriding all model or optimization library values.

data.name: ExplicitConeVoltage
data.value: The exact desired cone voltage (Waters instruments only) to be used in SRM methods or transitions lists for a target.

data.name: ExplicitDeclusteringPotential
data.value: The exact desired declustering potential (SCIEX instruments only) to be used in SRM methods or transitions lists for a target, overriding all model values.

data.name: ExplicitDriftTimeHighEnergyOffsetMsec
data.value: The exact desired drift time high energy offset (in milliseconds) to be used in extracting chromatograms from ion mobility high-energy mass spectra, overriding all model values.

data.name: ExplicitDriftTimeMsec
data.value: The exact desired drift time (in milliseconds) to be used in extracting chromatograms from ion mobility mass spectra, overriding all model values.

data.name: ExplicitGlobalStandardArea
data.value: Value to use when calculating "ratio to global standards". Use this when you want to normalize peak areas in a particular replicate by dividing by a value that you calculated outside of Skyline.

data.name: ExplicitIonMobility
data.value: The ion mobility value of the center of the filter window used when extracting chromatograms

data.name: ExplicitIonMobilityHighEnergyOffset
data.value: The ion mobility high energy offset to be used when extracting chromatograms

data.name: ExplicitIonMobilityUnits
data.value: The units of the Explicit Ion Mobility values.

data.name: ExplicitRetentionTime
data.value: The exact predicted retention time (in minutes) to be used for a target, overriding all other methods of prediction.

data.name: ExplicitRetentionTimeWindow
data.value: The exact desired retention time window (in minutes) to be used for a target, overriding all other settings used to derive this value.

data.name: ExplicitSLens
data.value: The exact desired SLens value (Thermo instruments only) to be used in SRM methods or transitions lists for a target.

data.name: Features
data.value: Collection of properties of the peak group which can be assigned a numerical score to be used in assessing peak quality.

data.name: FiguresOfMerit
data.value: The limits of detection and quantification for the peptide or molecule. The method for calculating these quantities can be chosen on the Quantification tab of the Peptide Settings.

data.name: FileIndex
data.value: File Index

data.name: FileName
data.value: The name of the file from which the data was imported

data.name: FilePath
data.value: The full path and file name of the file from which the data was imported.

data.name: Files
data.value: Files

data.name: FirstPosition
data.value: The position of the first (N-terminal) amino acid of the peptide within its containing protein sequence, or #N/A if no protein sequence is available.

data.name: FoldChange
data.value: The fold change value. The fold change is the ratio of the normalized intensity of the treatment group to the normalized intensity of the control group.

data.name: FoldChangeResult
data.value: Result of comparing values between the two groups.

data.name: FragmentIon
data.value: The name of the product ion peptide fragment (e.g. y8, y10, b7, etc.).

data.name: FragmentIonOrdinal
data.value: Position of the amino acid in the peptide after (C-terminal of) which the peptide was cleaved upon fragmentation. (e.g. 8, 10, 7, etc.)

data.name: FragmentIonType
data.value: The type of the product ion (y, b, c, z, a, x, precursor)

data.name: FullNames
data.value: The modified sequence where modifications are referred to by their full names, e.g. "C[Carbamidomethyl (C)]".

data.name: FullScanFilterWidth
data.value: Full Scan Filter Width

data.name: Fwhm
data.value: Full width at half max (FWHM) for the transition peak.

data.name: FwhmDegenerate
data.value: Fwhm Degenerate

data.name: Group
data.value: Value of the replicate annotation of the replicates that were compared to the control group.

data.name: Height
data.value: The maximum intensity of the points between the transition peak integration boundaries.

data.name: HMDB
data.value: Standardized molecular identifier

data.name: Identified
data.value: True if a MS/MS peptide identification exists for the result file at a time between the peak integration boundaries.

data.name: InChI
data.value: Standardized molecular identifier

data.name: InChiKey
data.value: Standardized molecular identifier

data.name: InstrumentSerialNumber
data.value: The instrument serial number read from an imported result file

data.name: Intensities
data.value: Comma separated list of chromatogram intensities.

data.name: Intercept
data.value: Y-intercept in the fitted line or curve

data.name: InternalStandardConcentration
data.value: Quantity of internal standard in the sample.

data.name: InterpolatedData
data.value: Chromatogram data which was interpolated in the time dimension so that the retention times are evenly spaced, and all transitions within the peptide or molecule have the same number of points.

data.name: InterpolatedIntensities
data.value: Chromatogram intensities from the interpolated data.

data.name: InterpolatedMassErrors
data.value: Chromatogram mass errors from the interpolated data.

data.name: InterpolatedNumberOfPoints
data.value: The number of points in the interpolated chromatogram.

data.name: InterpolatedSpectrumIds
data.value: Identifiers of the spectra that contributed to the points in the interpolated chromatogram.

data.name: InterpolatedTimes
data.value: The retention times in the interpolated chromatogram.

data.name: IonFormula
data.value: An atomic chemical formula for the fully charged (and possibly isotope labeled) ion to be measured in a mass spectrometer.

data.name: IonMobilityFragment
data.value: Center of the ion mobility filter window used in chromatogram extraction for a fragment ion. This may differ from the value for precursor ions , as fragment ions may move faster due to more energetic collisions,

data.name: IonMobilityHighEnergyOffset
data.value: The high energy offset for the precursor from the ion mobility library

data.name: IonMobilityMS1
data.value: Center of the ion mobility filter window used in chromatogram extraction for a precursor ion.

data.name: IonMobilityUnits
data.value: Units for ion mobility used in chromatogram extraction.

data.name: IonMobilityValue
data.value: The ion mobility of the precursor

data.name: IonMobilityWindow
data.value: Width of the ion mobility filter window used in chromatogram extraction.

data.name: IonName
data.value: The name of the precursor.

data.name: IsDecoy
data.value: True if this is a decoy precursor.

data.name: IsotopeDistIndex
data.value: Zero for the monoisotopic peak, 1 for M+1, 2 for M+2, etc.

data.name: IsotopeDistProportion
data.value: The proportion of the entire isotope distribution predicted for this isotope peak. Currently only available for precursor transitions filtered from high resolution MS1 scans.

data.name: IsotopeDistRank
data.value: The rank based on the IsotopeDistProportion among all isotope peaks for the predicted isotope distribution, shown in the user interface as “(irank #)”. Currently only available for precursor transitions filtered from high resolution MS1 scans.

data.name: IsotopeDotProduct
data.value: The dot-product calculation described above, but between the individual precursor (M, M+1, M+2, etc.) peak areas of the precursor and the intensities of the predicted isotope distribution, or #N/A if the transition is not a precursor isotope, or the chromatogram was not extracted from high resolution MS1 data.

data.name: IsotopeLabelType
data.value: A label type name associated with the precursor ion (light/heavy), indicating which isotope modifications are applied

data.name: KEGG
data.value: Standardized molecular identifier

data.name: Key
data.value: Key

data.name: Kurtosis
data.value: A measure of the "tailedness" of the chromatogram peak.

data.name: LastPosition
data.value: The position of the last (C-terminal) amino acid of the peptide within its containing protein sequence, or #N/A if no protein sequence is available

data.name: LibraryCollisionCrossSection
data.value: The collision cross section for the precursor from the ion mobility library

data.name: LibraryDotProduct
data.value: Equivalent to "dotp" displayed in the user interface. The dot-product between the individual transition peak areas of the precursor and the intensities of the matching ion peaks in the matched MS/MS spectral library spectrum (Note: as of v1.4, this is now 1 – Arcos(dotp)/(Pi/2) where dotp is the value described above. a.k.a. Normalize Spectrum Contrast Angle), or #N/A if the precursor has not matching library spectrum or has fewer than 4 transitions. This is a 35 useful value for method refinement. It works best when 6 or more transitions are present.

data.name: LibraryIntensity
data.value: The MS/MS peak intensity corresponding to the transition product ion in the matching library spectrum.

data.name: LibraryIonMobility
data.value: The ion mobility information for the precursor from the ion mobility library

data.name: LibraryIonMobilityHighEnergyOffset
data.value: The high energy offset for the precursor from the ion mobility library

data.name: LibraryIonMobilityUnits
data.value: The units of the Library Ion Mobility Value

data.name: LibraryIonMobilityValue
data.value: The ion mobility of the precursor from the ion mobility library

data.name: LibraryName
data.value: The name of a MS/MS spectral library, if a MS/MS spectral library spectrum is associated with the precursor ion.

data.name: LibraryProbabilityScore
data.value: The probability score assigned to this match in the input files used to build the spectral library.

data.name: LibraryRank
data.value: The rank based on LibraryIntensity of this transition among all transitions allowed by the transition Filter settings, shown in the user interface as “(rank #)”.

data.name: LibraryScore1
data.value: Raw peptide library score that may or may not be used to rank among precursors of a protein.

data.name: LibraryScore2
data.value: Raw peptide library score that may or may not be used to rank among precursors of a protein.

data.name: LibraryScore3
data.value: Raw peptide library score that may or may not be used to rank among precursors of a protein.

data.name: LibraryType
data.value: The type of MS/MS spectral library (BiblioSpec, GPM, NIST), if a MS/MS spectral library spectrum is associated with the precursor ion.

data.name: LimitOfDetection
data.value: The lower concentration limit at which the analyte can be reliably distinguished from a blank. The options about for calculating the lower limit of detection can be specified on the Quantification tab of the Peptide Settings.

data.name: LimitOfQuantification
data.value: The lower concentration limit where the analyte is said to be quantifiable. The options for determining this value can be specified on the Quantification tab of the Peptide Settings.

data.name: LinearFit
data.value: The result of doing the linear regression to determine the fold change.

data.name: Log2FoldChange
data.value: The logarithm base 2 of the fold change value.

data.name: Losses
data.value: A comma separated list of all neutral losses from this fragment

data.name: LossFormulas
data.value: A comma separated list of the chemical forumulas for all neutral losses from this fragment, or empty if not all losses have formulas

data.name: LossNeutralMass
data.value: The total mass of all neutral losses from this fragment.

data.name: MassErrorPPM
data.value: The difference between the expected and measured m/z values expressed in parts per million (PPM)

data.name: MassErrors
data.value: The mass errors of the chromatogram.

data.name: MatchingPrecursors
data.value: The subset of the selected precursors whose precursor m/z matches any of the spectra represented by the row in the Spectrum Grid.

data.name: Max
data.value: Max

data.name: MaxBestRetentionTime
data.value: Maximum of the precursor BestRetentionTime values

data.name: MaxDetectionQValue
data.value: A maximum of the false discovery rate (FDR) score assigned to each chosen target peak after applying a mPro phet model.

data.name: MaxEndTime
data.value: Maximum EndTime of all transitions for a precursor. Unless manually edited all transitions for a precursor use the same integration boundaries.

data.name: MaxFoldChange
data.value: The upper bound of the confidence interval of the fold change.

data.name: MaxFwhm
data.value: The maximum full width at half max (FWHM) of the transitions for the precursor.

data.name: MaxHeight
data.value: Max Height

data.name: MaxRetentionTime
data.value: Maximum of the transition RetentionTime values.

data.name: Mean
data.value: Mean

data.name: MeanArea
data.value: Mean of the transition Area values.

data.name: MeanAreaNormalized
data.value: Mean of the transition AreaNormalized values

data.name: MeanAreaRatio
data.value: Mean of the transition AreaRatio values.

data.name: MeanBestRetentionTime
data.value: Mean of the precursor BestRetentionTime values.

data.name: MeanFwhm
data.value: Mean of the transition Fwhm (peak width) values.

data.name: MeanMaxFwhm
data.value: Mean of the precursor MaxFwhm (peak width) values.

data.name: MeanMaxHeight
data.value: Mean Max Height

data.name: MeanRetentionTime
data.value: Mean of the transition RetentionTime values.

data.name: MeanTotalArea
data.value: Mean of the precursor TotalArea values.

data.name: MeanTotalAreaNormalized
data.value: Mean of the precursor TotalAreaNormalized values

data.name: MeanTotalAreaRatio
data.value: Mean of the precursor TotalAreaRatio values.

data.name: Median
data.value: Median

data.name: MedianDetectionQValue
data.value: A median of the false discovery rate (FDR) score assigned to each chosen target peak after applying a mProphet model.

data.name: MedianPeakArea
data.value: The median transition peak area of transition results in the particular result file. This median peak area is used when the normalization method is "Equalize Medians". If there is an internal standard label type, then the median peak area is calculated using only the peak areas from transitions whose precursor's label type is an internal standard. If there are no internal standard peak areas, then the median transition peak area is calculated from all transition peak areas.

data.name: Message
data.value: Warning, if any, of missing values that might impact comparisons of the "Raw" value between replicates.

data.name: Min
data.value: Min

data.name: MinBestRetentionTime
data.value: Minimum of the precursor BestRetentionTime values

data.name: MinDetectionQValue
data.value: A minimum of the false discovery rate (FDR) score assigned to each chosen target peak after applying a mProphet model.

data.name: MinFoldChange
data.value: The lower bound of the confidence interval of the fold change.

data.name: MinRetentionTime
data.value: Minimum of the transition RetentionTime values.

data.name: MinStartTime
data.value: Minimum StartTime of all transitions for a precursor. Unless manually edited all transitions for a precursor use the same integration boundaries

data.name: MissedCleavages
data.value: The number of missed cleavage sites in the peptide sequence

data.name: ModelScore
data.value: The sum of the feature values weighted according to the currently selected peak scoring model.

data.name: ModifiedAreaProportion
data.value: The normalized area of this peptide result divided by the sum of all peptide results in this protein and replicate that have the same unmodified sequence.

data.name: ModifiedSequence
data.value: Peptide sequence including any amino acid modifications such as cysteine alkylation. (example: AGLC[+57]QTFVYGGC[+57]R)

data.name: ModifiedSequenceAverageMasses
data.value: The modified sequence of the precursor where modifications are referred to by their average masses, e.g. "C[+57.05162]".

data.name: ModifiedSequenceFullNames
data.value: The modified sequence of the precursor where modifications are referred to by their full names, e.g. "C[Carbamidomethyl (C)]".

data.name: ModifiedSequenceMonoisotopicMasses
data.value: The modified sequence of the precursor where modifications are referred to by their monoisotopic masses, e.g. "C[+57.021464]".

data.name: ModifiedSequenceThreeLetterCodes
data.value: The modified sequence of the precursor where modifications are referred to by their three letter codes, e.g. "C[CAM]". If the modification does not have a three letter code, then its full name is used instead.

data.name: ModifiedSequenceUnimodIds
data.value: The modified sequence of the precursor where modifications are referred to by their unimod id, e.g. "C(unimod:4)". If the modification does not have a unimod id, then its full name is used instead.

data.name: ModifiedTime
data.value: Last time and date at which the original mass spectrometer file was modified on disk

data.name: Molecule
data.value: Molecules belong to Molecule Lists and contain Percursors.

data.name: MoleculeFormula
data.value: An atomic chemical formula for the neutral, unlabeled molecule to be measured in a mass spectrometer.

data.name: MoleculeList
data.value: A grouping of molecules in a Skyline document.

data.name: MoleculeListAbundance
data.value: A number representing the abundance of the molecule list, calculated according to the "Normalization Method" specified in the Molecule Quantification settings

data.name: MoleculeListAbundanceMessage
data.value: Warning if missing data impacts comparisons of "Molecule List Abundance" between replicates

data.name: MoleculeListAbundanceStrict
data.value: A number representing the abundance of the molecule list, calculated according to the "Normalization Method" specified in the Molecule Quantification settings. Unavailable when missing data impacts comparisons between replicates.

data.name: MoleculeListAbundanceTransitionAveraged
data.value: Average of the normalized areas of the transitions under the Molecule List. The areas are normalized according to the Normalization Method specified in the Molecule Quantification settings.

data.name: MoleculeListAbundanceTransitionSummed
